ion. And at first, it seems like everything is going great! You’ve got tons of opt-ins, loads of engagement, and people are obsessed with what you’re putting down. But then you go to pitch… And it’s crickets. Okay, okay, not totally crickets. You make some sales. But you’re well behind those hairy scary goals you set, and when you look at all of the work and money you put in, you start thinking to yourself: Is this even worth it? Can I be real with you? That freebie launch model that has you crossing your fingers And hoping for sales...has got to go. You know what I'm talking about, right? You pour your heart and soul into a free webinar, or even a 5-day challenge and give away a ton of POWERFUL and VALUABLE information. And at first, it seems like everything is going great! You’ve got tons of opt-ins, loads of engagement, and people are obsessed with what you’re putting down. But then you go to pitch… And it’s crickets. Okay, okay, not totally crickets. You make some sales. But you’re well behind those hairy scary goals you set, and when you look at all of the work and money you put in, you start thinking to yourself: Is this even worth it? It's Time To Kiss The Freebie Seekers Goodbye. Because honestly… there’s a much better way of launching . You know, one that doesn’t require you to… 01 Cross your fingers and HOPE that people convert after you’ve spent time and money giving them a shit ton of value (why are we settling for 2-4% anyway?!) 02 Switch launch strategies constantly throughout the year because you’re chasing a better conversion rate or that good ol’ novelty factor. 03 Drain your bank account trying to pay for ads that you’re not even sure you’ll make your money back on by the time everything is said and done. 04 Burn yourself out dealing with difficult clients who aren't a right fit for your offer (but end up buying anyway). Have Bigger Launches It's Time To Kiss The Freebie Seekers Goodbye. Because honestly… there’s a much better way of launching . Yo