https://www.bbcmaestro.com/courses/alan-moore/storytelling?utm_source=facebook&utm_medium=paidsocial&utm_campaign=%2ABM+%7C+TF+%7C+ACQ+%7C+Meta+%7C+Social+%7C+UK+%7C+EN+%7C+Discount+%7C+BAU+Variant&utm_content=ACQ_LAL-PurchasersSubscribers___1_VID_Value-15s_1_1_AM&fbclid=PAAab7S0iqLcc5jjip7c_oye_CC62HPoMlpwpnuq18rMKRrmDhQV_Un6WVE50_aem_ASTeKKI2r2Imb-wOyFOFeM4GeNQ1-zBubYchykyxymlBu6XMVkxUH-GAmDGpWEdberYEO9VTeY6d4z4BS2QXOOr6HMeSNvdx7spc7xmdldDbasH0TXdbH5pFBeuu5xTaMFs,Course (Paid) (Storytelling),"Learn storytelling from Alan Moore, the creator of ""Watchmen"" and ""V for Vendetta"".",Alan Moore | Storytelling | BBC Maestro,"Learn the craft of storytelling with literary maestro, Alan Moore. Discover how to build story, character, setting and plot in this online writing course.","Isabel Allende, Agatha Christie, Jojo Moyes, Ken Follett, Julia Donaldson, Lee Child, Harlan Coben, Bill Lawrence, Carol Ann Duffy, Malorie Blackman, Jed Mercurio, David Walliams, About, Support, Explore, Follow","Alan Moore | Storytelling | BBC Maestro Skip to main content Menu Close All Courses For business Already have an account? Log In Alan Moore Storytelling Create captivating stories with the internationally acclaimed author of V for Vendetta and Watchmen . This course includes: 6 hours 33 lessons 16 exercises Sorry, BBC Maestro is not yet available in your location Follow us for updates and availability announcements Find us on facebook Find us on instagram Find us on youtube What you&#39;ll learn Join Alan as he teaches you how to craft mesmerising stories, from finding compelling ideas to world-building for sci-fi and fantasy. Become a better writer Writing for different disciplines, from comics to poetry Find original ideas for your story Use powerful and inventive language Perfect narrative structure and format Embrace the tools of rhythm and rhetoric Your Maestro More like this This creative writing course comes from the incessantly imaginative bestseller, Alan Moore. His writing straddles genre with comics like From Hell, The League of Extraordinary Gentlemen and Swamp Thing, and modern literary classics, including Jerusalem, a 1,266-page experimental epic novel set over centuries and realms in his hometown of Northampton. He made it on to Time’s 100 Best Novels list and has won numerous awards leading to cult-like, legendary status and critical acclaim. Each morsel of wisdom out of Alan’s mouth will have you thinking in a new way. Isabel Allende Magical Storytelling Agatha Christie Writing Jojo Moyes Writing Love Stories Ken Follett Writing Bestselling Fiction Julia Donaldson Writing Children&#39;s Picture Books Lee Child Writing Popular Fiction Harlan Coben Writing Thrillers Bill Lawrence Writing Comedy for Television Carol Ann Duffy Writing Poetry Malorie Blackman Writing for Young Adults Jed Mercurio Writing Drama for Television David Walliams Writing Books for Children Previous Next Course preview Lesson plan (33) 01 Storytelling Introduction 06:56 02 Writing as enchantment 06:05 03 Becoming a writer 04:13 04 Four weapons 11:54 05 Learning to read 08:24 06 Imagination – fire of the gods 08:04 07 Language as technology 09:42 08 The neurology of writing 11:06 09 Hemingway vs. Baudelaire 09:00 10 Fascinating rhythm 13:39 11 Inventive language 09:39 12 Structure 10:26 13 Genre 08:15 14 Mode 11:42 15 Time and timing 08:29 16 Misdirection 14:20 17 Character 20:32 18 Extreme character 16:07 19 Place 18:04 20 Creating place 14:54 21 Period 17:21 22 Considering media 07:14 23 Comic cuts 23:47 24 Screen gems 23:38 25 Words, music and performance 12:53 26 Future media 05:15 27 The need for progress 08:13 28 Forward movements 05:12 29 Approaches to the future 10:25 30 Lost in the funhouse 14:13 31 The evolution of writing 03:30 32 Permission to write 04:39 33 Extroduction 03:51 Reviews for this course Explore all courses All courses New New Releases Writing Wellness &amp; Lifestyle Personal Development Food &amp; Drink Music, Film &amp; Theatre Business Art &amp; Design Previous Next for Business Inspire your team to grow with BBC Maestro Flexible packages for teams of 10 to 1,000 Pricing from just £24 per person per year Over 1,000 hours of content covering wellbeing, leadership, creativity, personal growth and more Get in touch Learn more Flexible packages for teams of 10 to 1,000 Pricing from just £24 per person per year Over 1,000 hours of content covering wellbeing, leadership, creativity, personal growth and more Common questions What is BBC Maestro? BBC Maestro is a subscription-based streaming platform, created to educate and inspire people to explore their creativity. Through pre-recorded lessons and detailed course notes, anyone can learn a wide range of disciplines and follow in the footsteps of experts respected all over the world. BBC Maestro offers single course purchases or an annual subscription. How does BBC Maestro work? Simply purchase an individual course or an All Courses pass and get access to easy-to-follow video lessons. Watch on your computer, tablet or mobile and learn on demand, wherever and whenever you like. Our courses are beginner-friendly and you can watch as many times as you like, at your own pace. Where is BBC Maestro available? BBC Maestro is currently available in the following territories: United Kingdom, Isle of Mann, Ireland, Jersey, Guernsey, Australia, South Africa, Canada, India, Brazil, Italy, Netherlands, Denmark, Spain, Germany, Belgium, Sweden, Switzerland, Portugal, Singapore, New Zealand, Hong Kong, UAE and USA. We are planning on launching BBC Maestro in other territories in the future. Please subscribe to our mailing list and follow our social media channels for updates. Is there a subscription? Yes, you can buy an annual subscription to get full access to all BBC Maestro courses, lessons and course notes for one year. Find out more Do courses have subtitles? Yes, all our courses have English subtitles that can be accessed by clicking the CC button on the video player. We also have downloadable PDF course notes to go with each course, which offer more detailed information and tips. Do courses have deadlines? No, all our courses are self-paced and no courses will be removed from the site. If you have an all-access annual subscription, you can watch any content while your subscription is valid. If you bought a single course, you will have access to the course for a year from your purchase date. The courses can be watched as many times as you like within your access period. Can I see a full list of available courses? Yes, you can see a full list of our current courses here. Can I get a subscription refund? We offer a 30-day money back guarantee for your first all-access annual subscription, if you aren't completely satisfied with your purchase. See our terms and conditions for details, or email support@bbcmaestro.com. What&#39;s the difference between buying a single course or a subscription? You can choose between buying a single course as a one-off purchase, or you can sign up for an annual subscription which gives you access to all BBC Maestro courses for one year. If you buy a single course, then you can access it for one year. You can watch the course as many times as you like, whenever you like. Our single courses include downloadable course notes to complement the video lessons. Your access to the course will expire after one year from the date of purchase. Alternatively, if you buy an annual subscription to BBC Maestro, you can access every course for one year. You can watch each course as many times as you like within the year, and you’ll also be able to download the course notes for each course. After one year you’ll have the option to renew your subscription, or you can choose not to renew once your subscription year is over. Subscriptions are billed annually, and we offer a 30-day money back guarantee to receive a full refund if you’re unhappy with your purchase. Does the subscription include upcoming courses? Subscribers will have instant access to new courses as they are released. Please note that any courses in the Upcoming Courses section may be released outside of your annual subscription period. If you have any questions about an upcoming course, please email support@bbcmaestro.com. How do gift cards work? You can buy a gift card for any individual course or an All Courses Pass on our gift cards page. When you buy a gift card, you can choose to send the email with the gift card PDF attached to yourself or directly to the recipient. You can specify which date you would like the gift card email to send to your recipient. Gift cards can be redeemed on the Gift Cards page. Once the card is redeemed, if the gift is for a single course the giftee will have one year's access to the course and be able to re-watch as many times as they like within that period. If the gift is for an All Courses Pass, the giftee will have one year’s access to all BBC Maestro courses, and immediate access to any new courses that are released within their yearly access period – from the date that they redeem their gift code. Please note, anyone outside of our available regions will not be able to redeem a gift card. Thanks for signing up. Check your inbox - your discount code is on the way! Oops! Something went wrong. Please try again later. Sign up to get free learning inspiration every month and 10% off your first order! Email Address Sign Up About Terms Privacy Cookies Careers Affiliates programme Business Support FAQs Contact Reviews Complaints Policy Students Groups Explore Articles Writing Courses Cooking Courses Sitemap Follow Facebook Instagram YouTube BBC Maestro is a commercial platform developed and operated by Maestro Media Ltd under licence from BBC Studios Distribution Ltd. BBC is a trademark of the British Broadcasting Corporation and is used under license. © 1996 © 2025. All rights reserved."
