INSTRUCTION We introduce the concepts, then teach you how to implement them in REAL cinematic projects. LIFETIME ACCESS Enrollment grants you instant access to all course content and future updates FOR LIFE, at no additional cost to you! WHAT YOU'LL LEARN IN THIS COURSE UNREAL ENGINE Benefit: Remember to speak to the benefits of each feature&nbsp; Feature: And how that speeds them to their desired result Benefit: &nbsp;What's your market desire most, what makes their mouth water? INDUSTRY-STANDARD WORKFLOWS LEARN FROM THE PROS: Learn to do things the RIGHT way, with cutting edge, industry-standard professional workflows&nbsp; LAND REAL JOBS: You'll be prepared to jump into any professional pipeline, workflow or studio as a filmmaker, VFX artist, game cinematics creator, and more. Benefit: &nbsp;What's your market desire most, what makes their mouth water? HOW TO CREATE CINEMATIC IMAGES INSIDER SECRETS: Learn the best-kept secrets to creating cinematic images through lighting, composition, and movement HANDS-ON PROJECTS: Put your knowledge to work as we create real, cinematic scenes step-by-step HOLLYWOOD-LEVEL VFX: &nbsp;Create Hollywood-level VFX using free tools and software COURSE BREAKDOWN DAY 1 - GETTING STARTED Basic terminology Key concepts in film &amp; visual effects Unreal Engine installation &amp; setup DAY 2 - THE BASICS Basic menus &amp; navigation in Unreal Engine Working with meshes, materials, shaders, and the building blocks of 3D graphics Achieving photorealism DAY 3 - CREATING YOUR FIRST SCENE Naming Conventions &amp; organization Landscape creation, lighting, cameras &amp; atmosphere Basic animation using Sequencer DAY 4 - SCENE BUILDING Creating Mood Boards Visual storytelling &amp; composition Advanced scene creation - Procedural Content Generation, building massive landscapes, adding foliage &amp; more Free sci-Fi building assets included! DAY 5 - LIGHTING Lighting Theory Hollywood lighting techniques HDRI Lighting Lighting massive scenes Create 3 cinematic lighting setups DAY 6 - ANIMATION Capturing High Quality Motion Capture at Home Creating Character Rigs (IK &amp; FK) Working with Metahumans Animation Retargeting Working with Motion Capture in Unreal Engine Character animation DAY 7 - SIMULATIONS Creating Realistic fire, smoke, explosions, &amp; water VST (VDB) workflows for Hollywood-level special effects Dynamic, real time fluid simulations in Unreal Engine DAY 8 - COMPOSITING 3D Camera Tracking Color management for accurate composites Compositing live-action footage &amp; CGI Composure - Compositing in Unreal Engine DAY 9 - RENDERING Prepare your scene for rendering Learn the secrets for achieving cinematic-quality renders every time Export render passes for compositing DAY 10 - POST PRODUCTION Color management Using render passes for more realistic composites Advanced compositing Cinematic color grading ENROLL NOW STILL NOT SURE? TRY IT BEFORE YOU BUY IT GET STARTED FOR FREE. Try the first 3 days of the Unreal Engine for Filmmakers course, completely free! Click below to sign up now! TRY IT FOR FREE Where should we send your free training? I agree to receive communications &amp; promotional emails from Boundless Entertainment Co. in accordance with the terms and conditions . SUBMIT LEARN THE FASTEST-GROWING TOOL IN THE FILM INDUSTRY Learn the same tools used by the pros on projects like The Batman , Dune 2 , Planet of the Apes and The Mandalorian . BUILD A CAREER IN FILM &amp; VFX You'll learn the secrets to creating incredible 3D worlds, as well as insider tricks on how to composite them with live-action footage for a seamless, photorealistic result. After taking this course, you’ll be equipped with all the skills you need to work in any professional setting, from Previz to VFX, filmmaking, and game cinematics. BUILD A CAREER IN FILM &amp; VFX After taking this course, you’ll be equipped with all the skills you need to work in any professional setting, from Previz to VFX, filmmaking, and game cinematics. ENROLL NOW MEET YOUR INSTRUCTOR SAM EISENHOWER I am an Indie Filmmaker at heart, and can't help but bring that do-it-yourself, gritty mentality to every project I work on. That's why I started Boundless Entertainment in 2021 - to help the gritty, creative, problem-solving Indie Filmmakers of the world to realize their visions at a level far exceeding their budgets, crew sizes, and resources. That desire to explore strange worlds and bring cinematic visions to life as an Indie Filmmaker has resonated with our 35,000+ followers, and grown our community to over 18,000 students who have trusted us with their education. I hope to provide a ton of value to your education with: 10+ years experience in the film &amp; VFX industry 3+ years experience teaching online courses In-person teaching experience as a University professor MY WORK TESTIMONIALS WHAT OTHERS ARE SAYING ""THIS CONTENT IS ABSOLUTELY PRICELESS"" “Sam’s course has completely altered the trajectory of my career. Not only has it made me more comfortable in a program previously unknown to me, but it allowed me to snag first place in a video contest hosted by Sam Kolder’s “Kolder Creative” and LensDistortions.com . The course is easy to follow and extremely user-friendly...To any filmmaker, whether you’re a beginner, like me, or a seasoned veteran in the industry, this content is absolutely priceless. It’s allowed me to bring my wildest dreams to life and can definitely do the same for you.” - Jacob Geeslin ""I STARTED OUT KNOWING NOTHING IN UNREAL ENGINE"" “I started out knowing nothing in unreal engine. With Sam's courses I've been able to create immaculate scenes in animation. It would be dumb to try and scavenge through YouTube tutorials as a beginner and not purchase this course. These courses sum up everything you need to know to get a good scene going, all while utilizing fundamentals in Unreal. Thank you Sam."" - Jarek N. ""HIS COURSES ARE WORTH THOUSANDS"" ""Amazing experience, Sam is a wonderful instructor and is such a knowledgeable individual. I went from zero 3D animation experience to making full movies! His courses are worth thousands but only cost a fraction of a fraction!"" - M.W. ""I SHOULD HAVE STARTED WITH THIS COURSE LONG AGO"" ""Been YouTubing all over the place into Unreal for two years now. I should have started with this course long ago. Sam exactly teaches what you need to know to become better faster. And I also had many questions which were unanswered are now answered. I highly recommend this course if you want to create jaw dropping scenes in Unreal. Great work Sam!"" - Sanderossi VIEW MORE REVIEWS WHAT'S INCLUDED VALUE-PACKED VIDEO TUTORIALS Gain instant access to over 30 hours of industry-leading video tutorials, accessible via our online portal any time of the day or night - for life. EXCLUSIVE COMMUNITY ACCESS Join a highly active community of over 18,000 satisfied students - from total beginners to professional artists. 24/7 SUPPORT Our dedicated customer support team is always there to help you with questions on course content, and even provide guidance for your personal projects! EXCLUSIVE DISCOUNTS &amp; DEALS Our partners have offered exclusive discounts and free trials of industry-leading tools such as Cree8 Virtual Workstations, Dehancer film emulation, and The Pixel Lab's high-quality simulation assets. This course literally pays for itself! PARTNERS GET INCREDIBLE DISCOUNTS FROM THESE BRANDS. CREE8 - VIRTUAL WORKSTATIONS DEHANCER - COLOR GRADING THE PIXEL LAB - VDB &amp; SIMULATION ASSETS CAREERS IN UNREAL ENGINE FILMMAKING VISUAL EFFECTS VIRTUAL PRODUCTION GAME CINEMATICS PREVIz CONTENT CREATION REVIEWS ENROLL NOW STILL NOT SURE? FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS We understand purchasing an online course is a big commitment. We're here to help. QUESTION 1: WHAT SKILL LEVEL IS THIS COURSE FOR? The Unreal Engine for Filmmakers course is for ANYONE. Whether you're a total beginner with no prior experience with 3D software or a seasoned veteran looking to learn more about Unreal Engine, this program is for YOU! QUESTION 2: HOW LONG DO I HAVE ACCESS TO THE COURSE AND WHEN DOES IT START? Enrollment in the course grants you instant access to all course content in the form of video tutorials. You can start immediately and move through the course at your own pace. There are no required ""class periods"" or classes you have to attend, and enrollment grants you access to all course content and future updates for life! QUESTION 3: WHAT JOBS CAN I GET AFTER TAKING THIS COURSE? Some common careers include: FILMMAKER - This course empowers solo creators and indie filmmakers to bring Hollywood-level visuals to their productions with a small team (or no team at all). VISUAL EFFECTS ARTIST - Unreal Engine for Filmmakers teaches you industry-standard techniques and workflows, so you're ready to jump into any pipeline or work opportunity. From commercials to TV shows to feature films, you'll be ready for anything! VIRTUAL PRODUCTION - Virtual Production is THE fastest-growing area of the film industry, expected to 3x in size by 2030. This course will teach you everything you need to know about Unreal Engine to work in a Virtual Production studio. GAME CINEMATICS ARTIST - Game studios rely heavily on the creation of high-quality cinematic trailers to sell their products. As a result, game cinematics creation is a key component at the heart of the gaming industry. This course is proven to prepare you for a rewarding career in game cinematics creation, with game studios like Blizzard Entertainment using it to train their cinematic artists in Unreal Engine. We seek to connect artists on our platform through our exclusive online community, and strongly encourage networking, job postings, and opportunities in the private group. You won't find these connections anywhere else! QUESTION 4: CAN'T I LEARN ALL OF THIS ON YOUTUBE? Technically, you could learn about 75% of this information on YouTube. However, the Unreal Engine for Filmmakers course is designed to save you WEEKS of time spent sorting through outdated, disorganized YouTube videos. It does so by providing a streamlined curriculum designed to teach you the important fundamental skills YouTube doesn't teach, then building upon those skills to take you from beginner to professional as quickly as possible. Time is your most valuable asset, and this course will pay for itself in no time! QUESTION 5: DON'T I NEED A POWERFUL COMPUTER TO USE UNREAL ENGINE? Enrollment in the&nbsp;Unreal Engine for Filmmakers course grants you a one month free trial of&nbsp; Cree8 &nbsp;– a service which provides users with high-powered virtual workstations. This allows you to learn Unreal Engine on ANY computer with an internet connection! Learn more at&nbsp; Cree8.io ! View Unreal Engine’s official documentation on this topic&nbsp; here . You do not need a supercomputer to run Unreal Engine, however when it comes to hardware, there are certain components that have a large impact on Unreal’s performance. As a result, below I’ve included both the REQUIRED hardware and the RECOMMENDED hardware for working in a professional setting. The required hardware is the minimum hardware you need to run Unreal Engine. The recommended hardware is the official hardware recommendation from Epic Games (the creators of Unreal Engine) for professional Unreal Engine artists, and is the typical hardware included in a computer running Unreal Engine at the Epic Games headquarters. Below is the REQUIRED hardware/software for running Unreal Engine: Operating system: Windows 10 64-bit Processor: Quad-core Intel or AMD 2.5 GHz or superior Memory: 8GB RAM Graphics Card: Any DirectX 11 or 12 compatible card Below is the RECOMMENDED hardware/software for running Unreal Engine: Operating system: Windows 10 64-bit (Version 20H2) Processor: Six-Core Xeon E5-2643 @ 3.4GHzMemory: 64 GB RAM Internal storage: 256 GB SSD External Storage: 2TB SSD Graphics Card: NVIDIA GeForce RTX 2080 SUPER Note: if you are looking to build or purchase a computer for using Unreal Engine, the most important hardware for creating and rendering high-quality cinematic visuals in Unreal Engine is the graphics card (or GPU). If you have an NVIDIA RTX 2000 series card or above, or an AMD RX 6000 series card or above, you will be able to take advantage of Hardware Ray Tracing, which results in more realistic lighting in your scene. This is not required, and Unreal’s alternative lighting methods are rapidly improving with every release, however Hardware Ray Tracing will give you the best results. The better your computer, the smoother Unreal Engine will perform! QUESTION 6: IS THERE A REFUND POLICY? If you are not 100% satisfied with the Unreal Engine for Filmmakers course, let us know within 7 days and we will refund your purchase, no questions asked. We pride ourselves in our products and want to serve this community to the best of our ability. If there's anything we can do to improve your experience, feel free to let us know. Enroll Now TRY IT RISK FREE 7-DAY MONEY BACK GUARANTEE If you are not 100% satisfied with the Unreal Engine for Filmmakers course, let us know within 7 days and we will refund your purchase. We stand behind our products. Please read our Terms of Use for more details. FOLLOW US USEFUL LINKS PRODUCTS FAQ ABOUT US SUPPORT CONTACT US EMAIL POLICIES TERMS OF USE PRIVACY POLICY EARNINGS DISCLAIMER Copyright 2025. Boundless Entertainment Co.. All Rights Reserved."
