n tafsir and verified sources ✅Suggested prompts if you're not sure where to start ✅Built with scholars for trusted guidance ✅ Practical, actionable steps for real-life application Absolutely free, no subscription needed After weeks of beta testing and scholarly review, we're proud to make this available to everyone. This is just the beginning - we have many more exciting features launching in the coming months, insha'Allah. ➡️ Download Niyyah today and try Quran Chat - we'd love your feedback https://lnkd.in/e5UuCmhY #Quranchat : Any Question on Any Ayah! 19 2 Comments Like Comment Share Niyyah 3,264 followers 5mo Report this post What if I told you P lestine was written in the Quran? Watch till the end to see the striking resemblance between the People of the Ditch and the resistance of our brothers and sisters today. History repeats itself—but so does Allah’s promise …more 31 Like Comment Share Niyyah 3,264 followers 5mo Report this post Have you heard about this story behind Surah Al Masad? Learn more about the short Surahs of the Qur’an through our app ‘Niyyah’! We take the short Surahs of the Qur’an and break them down into short, fun quizzes so we can apply its lessons! Don’t believe me? Comment Niyyah and we’ll send it to you! …more 10 1 Comment Like Comment Share Niyyah 3,264 followers 8mo Report this post Thanks Deen Developers for hosting such a wonderful conversation - Ramadan Mubarak! ⭐✨💫 Deen Developers 11,489 followers 8mo Edited Ramadan Mubarak from Deen Developers! 🌙 Ramadan is here—a time for reflection, growth, and building what truly matters. We couldn’t have asked for a better way to lead into this blessed month than with our incredible community at why i built this. a huge shoutout to Shinaz Navas , founder of Niyyah , for sharing his building journey with Taz Latif on intention and using technology to remove barriers between us and our faith. As we step into this month, let’s remember that the best things we build aren’t just products — they’re habits, relationships, and impact that last beyond ramadan. may this be a month of barakah, breakthroughs, and big ideas for us all. Big big thank you to Cur8 Capital for hosting us on the night! Ibrahim Khan Muhammad Altalib Excited to see Niyyah 's #20in20 campaign in action—helping more muslims connect with the quran in their daily lives. Check it out and get involved: onelink.to/9jsfjj #ramadanmubarak #whyibuiltthis #startuplife #muslimtech 7 Like Comment Share Niyyah reposted this Shinaz Navas Understand and apply the Quran in &lt;5 mins a day | CEO of Niyyah 10mo Report this post 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗡𝗶𝘆𝘆𝗮𝗵 𝘁𝗲𝗮𝗺 𝗶𝘀 𝗴𝗿𝗼𝘄𝗶𝗻𝗴! 🌱 We're looking for a Content Lead to join us in transforming how millions engage with the Quran. Here's what gets me excited: Every piece of content we create has the potential to help someone understand Allah's words better. Imagine the impact of helping millions engage with the Quran in a meaningful way to not just transform their lives but the lives of others around them. Alhamdulillah, we're already seeing this impact. Our community of 50,000+ users tell us they're discovering new meanings and practical lessons from the Quran in just 5 minutes a day. But we know this is just the beginning – there are 2 billion Muslims who could benefit from understanding the Quran better. If you're passionate about Islamic content and want your work to have lasting impact in both this life and the next, this could be for you. You'll be joining a high-performing team of 18 that are on a mission to help millions understand and apply the Quran. The best part? This isn't just another content role. You have the opportunity to become a core part of the leadership team, shape Niyyah's future, and ultimately make the Quran accessible at a scale that has never been achieved before insha'Allah. That's the kind of impact that lasts beyond our lifetime. Want to be part of this journey? Check out the full role details in the comments 👇 PS - Please share with anyone you think coul