https://trinakavanagh.com/2024/04/23/the-truth-behind-belief-coding-is-it-a-cult-or-a-community/,Service (e-Book) (Blog),"Trina Kavanagh's Blog: An article exploring the concept of 'belief coding,' discussing whether it is more akin to a cult or a community.","The Truth Behind Belief Coding® &#8211; Is it a Cult or a Community? &#8211; Trina Kavanagh &#8211; Nottingham Healer, Categories, Tags, search, previous, next, tag, category, expand, menu, location, phone, mail, time, cart, zoom, edit, close","The author reflects on the labeling of positive groups as cults and shares their experience with Belief Coding®. They emphasize the importance of personal experience and highlight the positive aspects of the program. The author believes that genuine positive groups, including Belief Coding®, prioritize safety, freedom of choice, and love.","The Truth Behind Belief Coding® &#8211; Is it a Cult or a Community?, Share this:, Related, Leave a comment Cancel reply, Post navigation, Subscribe to Blog via Email","The Truth Behind Belief Coding® &#8211; Is it a Cult or a Community? &#8211; Trina Kavanagh &#8211; Nottingham Healer Skip to content Trina Kavanagh &#8211; Nottingham Healer Empowering Leaders to Reach their Goals Menu Home Nottingham Healer Services Store Blog LinkedIn Youtube Instagram April 23, 2024 February 13, 2025 Trina Kavanagh-Thomas Leave a Comment on The Truth Behind Belief Coding® &#8211; Is it a Cult or a Community? The Truth Behind Belief Coding® &#8211; Is it a Cult or a Community? Observations, over the years I have noticed groups form. Many groups that become big and do very well and have lots of positive people can be labelled as cults. There are many groups where people are genuinely happy and sometimes many are NOT. But, does that mean some groups (like Belief Coding®) are a cult? What is Belief Coding®? Jessica Cunningham&#8217;s Belief Coding® is a modality that transforms the beliefs and feelings that stop us from moving forward in life. By working with the memories that hold us back, we can release, shift and imprint brand-new points of view that enable us to see life from a new and more confident perspective. Is Belief Coding® a Cult? When I joined Belief Coding® , I felt the same. I had practised many modalities and felt that this would not cover the rest. I felt sceptical with all the cheeriness but nonetheless… that first session just blew my mind that I had to invest. Since then I have developed a deeper level of trust in the program, the people and the facilitators. Not everyone has had a great experience in groups. I am not saying that everyone&#8217;s opinion doesn&#8217;t count. Not everyone is going to like something or LOVE something and that is ok. Does that mean that something is a cult? No. Not always. Read here about what makes a group a cult . Cults are dangerous and I personally feel this word gets banded about when there are serious cults actually going under the radar. What makes a positive group? It is safe enough for you to be heard, listened to and seen People come to connect and make friendships Clarity and honesty You can leave and retain your own free will What makes Belief Coding® different? Currently doing scientific research to stay on the curve of healing Clear that this is NOT therapy but facilitation S afeguarding is important Leads with love, not hate Gives others a voice To finalise, everyone will have issues with groups. However, many groups (including Belief Coding®) work extremely hard to create a positive, safe and inclusive environment that promotes the free will of those within it. I would love to invite you to check out Belief Coding as a leader so you can reach your goals with empowering new beliefs, by booking a call here &#8211; Book a call Trina x Energy and Goal Alignment Expert Share this: Click to share on X (Opens in new window) X Click to share on Facebook (Opens in new window) Facebook Click to share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window) LinkedIn More Click to share on Pinterest (Opens in new window) Pinterest Click to share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window) WhatsApp Like Loading... Related Published by Trina Kavanagh-Thomas Trina is a nongrammatical writer, coach and a SELF infused intuitive witch who loves all things natural and science-based. You can find Trina studying for her degree, talking to strangers and walking around the Nottinghamshire countryside with her husband, 3 children and many animals. View all posts by Trina Kavanagh-Thomas Categories business , life , relationships Tags Community , Personal Growth , Self Love Leave a comment Cancel reply &#916; Post navigation Next Are You Jumping in The Deep End? Stepping Outside Your Comfort Zone Subscribe to Blog via Email Enter your email address to subscribe to this blog and receive notifications of new posts by email. Email Address: Subscribe Join 2,146 other subscribers Website Powered by WordPress.com . Comment Reblog Subscribe Subscribed Trina Kavanagh - Nottingham Healer Join 130 other subscribers Sign me up Already have a WordPress.com account? Log in now. Privacy Trina Kavanagh - Nottingham Healer Subscribe Subscribed Sign up Log in Copy shortlink Report this content View post in Reader Manage subscriptions Collapse this bar %d search previous next tag category expand menu location phone mail time cart zoom edit close"
https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/my-wildest-prediction/id1717751596,Podcast ,Tom Goodwin's wildest digital predictions,My Wildest Prediction - Podcast - Apple Podcasts,Listen to Euronews,"My Wildest Prediction, Episodes, My Wildest Prediction: Second season wrap-up, 'Neurotech will change how we live,' predicts Neuroelectrics CEO Ana Maiques, 'US voters will cast their ballots by smartphones within eight years', businessman Andrew Yang says, 'AI isn't a threat', says former Netflix HR Chief Patty McCord, ‘By 2080, 90% of people will live in cities’ Urbanist Greg Clark says, 'The productivity fetish will end' work futurist Dom Price says, ‘People will stop making predictions’ David Spiegelhalter says, ‘The next Microsoft will be started by a 17-year-old girl,’ with entrepreneur Tara Chklovski, Trailer, Introducing My Wildest Prediction, Ratings &amp; Reviews, Great slices of human motivations, Great first episode topic…, About, Information, Africa, Middle East, and India, Asia Pacific, Europe, Latin America and the Caribbean, The United States and Canada, Africa, Middle East, and India, Asia Pacific, Europe, Latin America and the Caribbean, The United States and Canada","My Wildest Prediction - Podcast - Apple Podcasts Home New Top Charts Search My Wildest Prediction Euronews 5.0 (3) ENTREPRENEURSHIP UPDATED SEMIMONTHLY From pocket-sized devices connecting the world to driverless cars roaming city streets — who could have imagined? Space tourism, gene editing, and more — all once wild dreams are now a reality. Join innovation expert Tom Goodwin on 'My Wildest Predictions' every other Wednesday starting November 22nd, as we explore the forefront of this ever-changing world with business and tech visionaries Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information. Latest Episode Follow Episodes JUN 18 My Wildest Prediction: Second season wrap-up The second season of My Wildest Prediction, hosted by innovation expert Tom Goodwin, has come to an end. Here we share some of the key conclusions. In the following order, you can listen to: Tom Goodwin (host); Ana Maiques (CEO of Neuroelectrics); Nancy Xu (CEO of Moonhub); Patty McCord (HR Consultant); Bruce Daisley (Author); Dom Price (Work Futurist); Karoli Hindriks (CEO of Jobbatical); Susan Kahn (Business Psychologist); Scott Galloway (Business Guru); Andrew Yang (Businessman); Tara Chklovski, (CEO of Technovation); Lukas Boni (Co-Founder of Planted); Greg Clark (Urbanist); Rory Sutherland (Marketing Expert); Bertrand Piccard (Aviator); David Spiegelhalter (Professor). My Wildest Prediction is a podcast series from Euronews Business where we dare to imagine the future with business and tech visionaries. Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information. 8 min JUN 4 'Neurotech will change how we live,' predicts Neuroelectrics CEO Ana Maiques Ana Maiques is the CEO and co-founder of Neuroelectrics, a European company developing innovative technologies to monitor and stimulate the brain to help people living with neurological diseases. She is widely recognised as one of Europe's most inspiring entrepreneurs. In 2014, she received the EU Prize for Women Innovators from the European Commission, and in 2015, Neuroelectrics was named Best Health Start-Up by Wired UK magazine. Today, Ana Maiques joins the show to talk about the present and the future of neurotechnology.&nbsp; My Wildest Prediction is a podcast series from Euronews Business where we dare to imagine the future with business and tech visionaries. Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information. 22 min MAY 21 'US voters will cast their ballots by smartphones within eight years', businessman Andrew Yang says Andrew Yang is a former United States presidential candidate.&nbsp;Founder of the non-profit organisations Humanity Forward and Venture for America, he is committed to the creation of a human-centred economy, and he wants to fix the broken US economy.&nbsp;He is the author of the New York Times bestseller&nbsp;The War on Normal People&nbsp;and helped to introduce the idea of universal basic income into the political mainstream. Today, Andrew Yang joins us on the show to talk about how digital voting could change the US political system. My Wildest Prediction is a podcast series from Euronews Business where we dare to imagine the future with business and tech visionaries. Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information. 18 min MAY 7 'AI isn't a threat', says former Netflix HR Chief Patty McCord Patty McCord is the former chief talent officer at Netflix, where she worked for 14 years.&nbsp;She co-created the Netflix Culture Deck, a presentation laying out the company’s values and a document that Sheryl Sandberg once called “the most important document ever to come out of Silicon Valley”.&nbsp;McCord is the author of Powerful: Building a Culture of Freedom and Responsibility, a best-selling book where she shares advice for leaders who want to build successful teams. Today, Patty McCord joins My Wildest Prediction to tell us her boldest views on the future regarding artificial intelligence (AI). Although many people fear the impact AI could have on society and jobs, Patty McCord is enthusiastic about the AI revolution and shares her thoughts on how it could enhance human creativity. My Wildest Prediction is a podcast series from Euronews Business where we dare to imagine the future with business and tech visionaries. Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information. 26 min APR 23 ‘By 2080, 90% of people will live in cities’ Urbanist Greg Clark says Greg Clark is a highly renowned UK urbanist.&nbsp;He is, among others, chair of the Connected Places Catapult, a board member of Transport for London, and a Chair of Places for London and 3Ci, the City Commission for Climate Investment.&nbsp;Clark is also an author and global advisor who has worked with cities, national governments, and organisations such as the OECD, the Brookings Institution, and the World Bank. Today, he joins us on the show to discuss how and where we will live in the future.&nbsp; My Wildest Prediction is a podcast series from Euronews Business where we dare to imagine the future with business and tech visionaries. Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information. 30 min APR 9 'The productivity fetish will end' work futurist Dom Price says Dom Price is a work futurist at Atlassian, an American software company based in Sydney, Australia.&nbsp;With experience spanning technology, finance, and gaming, Dom brings a unique perspective to the future of work. As a sought-after media commentator and keynote speaker, he shares his insights on life, and the evolving job landscape, helping individuals and companies rethink their approach to success. Since predicting the future of work is at the core of Dom’s mission, we couldn’t pass up the opportunity to invite him to My Wildest Prediction. My Wildest Prediction is a podcast series from Euronews Business where we dare to imagine the future with business and tech visionaries. Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information. 24 min MAR 26 ‘People will stop making predictions’ David Spiegelhalter says David Spiegelhalter is one of the world's most important figures in statistics. He's an emeritus professor of statistics in the Centre for Mathematical Studies at the University of Cambridge and he's the author of The Art of Uncertainty: How to Navigate Chance, Ignorance, Risk and Luck. Spiegelhalter is committed to making mathematics more accessible, and he joins My Wildest Prediction to talk about probabilities, how to deal with uncertainty and artificial intelligence. My Wildest Prediction is a podcast series from Euronews Business where we dare to imagine the future with business and tech visionaries. Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information. 24 min MAR 12 ‘The next Microsoft will be started by a 17-year-old girl,’ with entrepreneur Tara Chklovski Tara Chklovski is the founder and CEO of Technovation, a global non-profit empowering young women to tackle real-world problems through technology and entrepreneurship. Chklovski joins My Wildest Prediction to explain how technology and education can spark positive change in underrepresented communities. My Wildest Prediction is a podcast series from Euronews Business where we dare to imagine the future with business and tech visionaries. Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information. 20 min See All (30) Trailer TRAILER Introducing My Wildest Prediction Dating apps will die, capitalism is over, and social apps will slowly disappear... Get ready for some very wild predictions from the world's tech and business leaders as they chat about the future with innovation expert Tom Goodwin. Subscribe now and dare to imagine the future world with us every other Wednesday, starting November 22nd. Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information. S1 • 1 min Ratings &amp; Reviews 5 out of 5 3 Ratings Great slices of human motivations 01/14/2024 John N81 Tom gets to why humans/consumers/users or whatever you want to group them as for your work, do what they want to do. This podcast is a great break from the plethora of shows talking about how humans do things and really gets into their brains. I like Tom’s relaxed style of interviewing, and so far, broad range of subjects. No idea what’s coming next and that’s great! Great first episode topic… 11/27/2023 Info_Sprinkles Love the opening jingle as well. Can’t wait for your quantum computing prediction episode! Cheers About From pocket-sized devices connecting the world to driverless cars roaming city streets — who could have imagined? Space tourism, gene editing, and more — all once wild dreams are now a reality. Join innovation expert Tom Goodwin on 'My Wildest Predictions' every other Wednesday starting November 22nd, as we explore the forefront of this ever-changing world with business and tech visionaries H