pts SEOs to reconsider their roles in an AI-first landscape. He leaves readers with critical questions to navigate this evolving environment effectively. Dive in to learn how to stay ahead as you plan your campaigns during these evolutionary times. Source: Search Engine Journal 5 1 Comment Like Comment Share Copy LinkedIn Facebook Twitter To view or add a comment, sign in Usama Khan B2B and SaaS Content Strategist &amp; Writer 4mo Report this post My article for a SaaS platform just made it to AI overview, and here’s what you need to know: Unhappy SaaS customers often search “X alternatives”. “X Alternatives” hijacks your competitor’s target audience. In terms of content: Think of all the pain points regarding the main keyword, and answer them in your content naturally (this makes it easier for AI to extract context-based info from within your article). The Winning Formula: → Structure your content to answer user questions directly. → Focus on EEAT. Go beyond basic definitions. Provide in-depth explanations, real-world examples, and insightful comparative analysis. → Implement schema markup to provide structured data to search engines. That’s what triggers AI overview for you to claim the spot! 4 2 Comments Like Comment Share Copy LinkedIn Facebook Twitter To view or add a comment, sign in Milestone Inc 67,679 followers 5mo Edited Report this post Top Search Marketing Priorities for 2025 We caught up with Fabrice Canel , Principal Program Manager at Bing, to discuss what search marketers need to focus on as we approach 2025. Here are his key insights: 1️ Adopt IndexNow – Take control of indexing for faster updates and cleaner SERPs. 2️ Prioritize Quality – AI-driven content is booming, but authority and relevance are key. 3️ Leverage Schema – Structured data helps search engines understand your content deeply. 4️ Embrace AI – Use AI to optimize, rephrase, and personalize content to match user intent. 5️ Zero-Click Strategy – Optimize for SERPs that deliver value while encouraging site visits. The future is all about quality, automation, and conversion-driven strategies. Are you ready? #DigitalMarketing #SearchTrends #SearchMarketing #AI #SEO2025 …more Top 5 Search Marketing Strategies for 2025 | Insights from Fabrice Canel, Bing 14 Like Comment Share Copy LinkedIn Facebook Twitter To view or add a comment, sign in CallRail 23,934 followers 1y Edited Report this post We are proud to announce the launch of our newest AI-powered report: multi-conversation insights! 🔬 Delivered directly to your inbox, multi-conversation insights surface AI-generated findings that reveal key trends, opportunities, and risks in campaign-based conversations over the past week. Multi-conversation insights report, available with Premium Conversation IntelligenceTM, boosts marketers' efficiency by automatically providing insights from multiple conversations and establishes a new benchmark for conversational AI capabilities. Multi-conversation insights give businesses visibility into specific source information over the past 7 days, such as: ▪️ 3–6 sentence summaries to give marketers a quick, accurate overview of what types of conversations a campaign is driving. ▪️ Average sentiments of calls in a campaign each week and identification of trends driving positive or negative customer satisfaction. ▪️ Commonly asked questions that will drive businesses’ SEO and keyword strategy, marketing messaging and product offerings. To learn more about our latest AI report multi-conversation insights, visit this link: https://bit.ly/3wAt2iW 10 1 Comment Like Comment Share Copy LinkedIn Facebook Twitter To view or add a comment, sign in Aniket Karmakar 🚀 Driving 20%+ Business Growth | Digital Marketing &amp; CRM Expert | Founder@ Pixxel Pod &amp; Crux Ops | Trainer @ Seven Boats Academy 5mo Report this post 🚀 Simplify Product Development with AI Building products people actually want can feel like a guessing game—but it doesn’t have to be. With AI, you can tap into re