onential! 💠AI vs. ML vs. DL - Demystified: 🔸Artificial Intelligence (AI): The broad concept of machines performing tasks that typically require human intelligence. 🔸Machine Learning (ML): A subset of AI that focuses on systems learning from data without explicit programming. 🔸Deep Learning (DL): A subfield of ML that uses neural networks with many layers (hence ""deep"") to learn complex patterns, especially effective with unstructured data like images, sound, and text. It's amazing how interconnected these fields are! Feeling energized after this first deep dive. Looking forward to what tomorrow brings! What are your thoughts on the most impactful ML application you've seen? Share in the comments! 👇 #MachineLearning #AI #DeepLearning #DataScience #LearningJourney #Day1 #Tech #Innovation 8 Like Comment Share Copy LinkedIn Facebook X To view or add a comment, sign in Kim Schlesinger Tech Educator 3w Edited Report this post Generative AI tools like Cursor , GitHub Copilot, and Claude are changing how software gets built. What does that mean for developer education, especially learning through open source contributions? Last summer, Phoebe Quincy and I explored this at Open Source Summit North America. We examined how AI shifts the skills learners need, how open source can remain a hands-on learning pathway, and what learners and maintainers should adjust in the age of AI. Watch the talk: https://lnkd.in/gCCk_Vvs See the slides: https://lnkd.in/gtiCivVS #OpenSource #DeveloperEducation #GenerativeAI #AIEducation #OSSCommunity #SoftwareEngineering 38 Like Comment Share Copy LinkedIn Facebook X To view or add a comment, sign in Thudimilla Sai kiran Attended Osmania University 1mo Report this post 🚀 Excited to share ""Machine Learning for Absolute Beginners - Level 1"" — a perfect starting point for anyone curious about diving into the world of AI and machine learning! No prior experience needed. This course breaks down complex concepts into simple, easy-to-understand lessons designed to build a strong foundation. Whether you’re a student, professional, or just eager to learn, this Level 1 course will guide you step-by-step through the basics of machine learning. #MachineLearning #AI #Beginners #DataScience #Learning #TechSkills 6 Like Comment Share Copy LinkedIn Facebook X To view or add a comment, sign in Suman Debnath Technical Lead, ML @ Anyscale 2w Edited Report this post Distributed training isn’t always easy to grasp at first, from the underlying infrastructure challenges to the variety of techniques that make large-scale training possible. Today, at the Ray x DeepSpeed: AI at Scale event following the PyTorch Conference, I had the opportunity to discuss different distributed training techniques, focusing on Data Parallelism (DDP, ZeRO-1/2/3, and FSDP) and how you can seamlessly implement them with Ray and PyTorch. My colleague Masahiro Tanaka , then shared insights on SuperOffload, a novel offloading technique for Superchips, and also demonstrated how we can fine-tune an LLM with Ray Train and DeepSpeed, truly exciting advancements for scaling AI efficiently. It was great to connect with the community and exchange ideas on how we can make distributed training more accessible and powerful. Distributed Training at Scale with Ray (short version): https://lnkd.in/eVEAgX2K Fine-tune an LLM with Ray Train and DeepSpeed : https://lnkd.in/exmQ3GQf SuperOffload : https://lnkd.in/exriwfJB 105 1 Comment Like Comment Share Copy LinkedIn Facebook X To view or add a comment, sign in 243,472 followers 477 Posts View Profile Follow Explore related topics How to Learn Artificial Intelligence Without a Degree Top Learning Resources for AI Enthusiasts AI Learning Roadmap for Newcomers Explore content categories Career Productivity Finance Soft Skills &amp; Emotional Intelligence Project Management Education Technology Leadership Ecommerce User Experience Show more Show less LinkedIn &copy; 2025 About Accessibility User Agreement Privacy Policy 