nth venture: 1️⃣ Spot Your Own Bottlenecks First Before you build for others, identify where AI could save you hours. Drafting emails, Summarizing reports, Automating repetitive data entry If AI can remove your manual work, chances are it can do the same for 100 other businesses. This is how you find your niche. 2️⃣ Launch an AI Automation Venture You don’t need to be a coder. Tools like ChatGPT, Claude, or AutoGPT make building automation simple. Your job isn’t to reinvent AI it’s to apply it. Think: “How can this tool reduce cost, save time, or make better decisions for a business?” That’s your offer. 3️⃣ Build Custom AI Solutions for Businesses Businesses don’t want “general AI.” They want AI trained on their data. Train on sales records → Predict revenue trends. Train on customer chats → Build support bots. Train on website traffic → Spot drop-offs before they cost money. Frameworks like PyTorch, TensorFlow, or fine-tuned GPT models can help here. 4️⃣ Expand Into Multiple Solutions Once you’ve cracked one automation, stack more: AI chatbots for support, Predictive analytics for growth, Personalized recommendations for sales. Each service builds on the same foundation but deepens your revenue streams. 5️⃣ Don’t Ignore Small Businesses AI isn’t just for Fortune 500s.Local shops can automate customer follow-ups.Startups can save thousands by replacing repetitive workflows with AI. This is the underserved market that most automation firms overlook. 6️⃣ Add Training as a Revenue Stream Once you’ve built solutions, teach businesses how to run their own private AI. Workshops. Online training, Retainers for ongoing support, Not only do you earn from services, but you also position yourself as a trusted partner. The Big Picture : AI isn’t about knowing how to code.It ’s about spotting where manual effort → automation → efficiency → profit. If you start today, you’ll be ahead of 95% of people who are still waiting to “figure AI out.” Repost this to help your network, Follow Uttam Gupta for more such content. #ai #professionals #automation 195 21 Comments Like Comment Share Copy LinkedIn Facebook X To view or add a comment, sign in Sana Singh I draw from design and strategy, tested in delivery — now asking how AI really makes marketing work | ~8 years of experience across FMCG, D2C, Digital Consulting and HR Tech 1mo Report this post Love this take on AI as a personal task automator. It starts with the tiny things — drafting an email, planning meals, summarising notes — and before you know it, you’ve built a system that quietly scales into how your team or business runs. What struck me is how invisible these shifts feel. You don’t suddenly wake up with a new workflow. You just wake up one day and realise you haven’t done that workflow in months — the agent has. That’s the thread I’m chasing in my own #WhereIsAI series: not the sci-fi future of AI, but the quiet rewiring of our daily rituals. For me, it already shows up in ways like: Eyes, saved — a custom list of screen settings across my devices to cut blue light and make dynamic shifts even more personalised. Dietary guardrail — flagging hidden whey/soy when I scan food labels, remembering my grocery staples, and prepping a Sunday refill list. Fitness stitched in — suggesting safer variations of exercises so I don’t aggravate an old knee injury. Curious — what’s the smallest everyday task AI has already taken over for you? Uttam Gupta Your #1 AI Solutions Partner - Helping businesses with AI Sales Voice Agents, Paid Ads &amp; Smart AI Automations | 👉 Book FREE 1:1 AI Strategy Call to Start (Link Below) 1mo Edited Everyone should own an AI automation venture that earns $500+ per day. Unfortunately, most people have no idea how to get started. Here’s the blueprint to go from knowing nothing about AI → building a $15,000/month venture: 1️⃣ Spot Your Own Bottlenecks First Before you build for others, identify where AI could save you hours. Drafting emails, Summarizing reports, Automati