Frustrated. Said their chatbot was giving wrong answers, their CRM was a mess, and customers were angrier than before they ""automated."" I asked one question: ""Did you document your process before automating it?"" 𝘚𝘪𝘭𝘦𝘯𝘤𝘦. Here's what most people don't understand: AI doesn't fix broken processes. It amplifies them. If your customer support is disorganized manually, automation will just make it disorganized faster. If your team doesn't know which questions customers ask most, your AI won't either. If your data is scattered across WhatsApp, emails, and random spreadsheets? Good luck training any system on that. So before you spend a dollar on AI, do this: → Document your top 10 customer questions (I call the rare ones OBMQs—Once in Blue Moon Questions 😅) → Map out your current process step-by-step (even the messy parts) → Identify what's repetitive vs. what needs human judgment → Organize your data in ONE place (Google Sheets, Notion, anywhere—just pick one) 𝗧𝗵𝗲𝗻 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗼𝗻𝗹𝘆 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗻,𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗰𝗮𝗻 𝗯𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝗜. Because here's the truth: A documented process + AI = 𝗲𝗳𝗳𝗶𝗰𝗶𝗲𝗻𝗰𝘆 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗴𝗿𝗼𝘄𝘁𝗵 A messy process + AI = 𝗲𝘅𝗽𝗲𝗻𝘀𝗶𝘃𝗲 𝗱𝗶𝘀𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗿 I've seen businesses waste $5K-$10K automating the wrong things because they skipped this step. 𝗗𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗯𝗲 𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗺. 𝗣.𝗦. If you're thinking about AI automation but not sure where to start, I help businesses audit their processes first before building anything. Comment ""𝗔𝗨𝗗𝗜𝗧"" and I'll send you a simple checklist I use with clients. No charge, just want to help you avoid costly mistakes. #AIAutomation #CustomerSupport #BusinessAutomation #ProcessImprovement #AI #SmallBusiness #Efficiency #n8n #AutomationStrategy #BusinessGrowth #TechForBusiness #DigitalTransformation #StartupTips #Entrepreneurship #ProductivityHacks #Business #AI 3 Like Comment Share Copy LinkedIn Facebook X To view or add a comment, sign in 710,257 followers 1,491 Posts View Profile Follow Explore related topics How to Create a Pitch Deck for Startup Funding Crafting a Compelling Pitch 