e &#8211; after starting Compact Keywords only two months ago. Everyone needs to take this. You will see results you can’t even comprehend. Jacob Darrah Jacob Darrah Why use the Compact Keywords Method? Target people looking to buy now Target decision makers representing a lot of people Low cost and low effort to perform Shows on page 1 of Google faster than normal Aligns with Google guidelines Works with AI, video, and user-generated content Startups, SMBs, Enterprise… All drive sales with the Compact Keywords method… Across software, services, ecom, local, finance, health, coaching, info products, so much more. All other SEO courses and gurus tell you to focus on blog SEO which… Has low conversion rates Takes a lot of time and money Is getting deprioritized by Google Algorithm Updates Is getting replaced by AI Blog SEO is NOT WORTH WHILE! Compact Keywords instead focuses on purchase-intent SEO landing pages which… Are designed from the ground up for getting customers, users, and leads Requires less time and money Are optimized for long-term success with Google Updates Gets recommended by AI Here’s why… Blog SEO = answering &ldquo;how, what, why, etc&rdquo; with SEO, then trying to convert those visitors. Compact Keywords SEO = scalable SEO landing pages for high-intent scenarios. NOT THIS THIS NOT THIS THIS NOT THIS THIS Designed from the ground up for getting customers, users, and leads By only targeting language that has high-purchase intent, Compact Keywords naturally becomes about offering your products or services as a direct solution to people who are already looking for them . Blog SEO, by contrast, answers “how, what, why” questions to people who are not ready to buy or use. Then it hopes to convert these people to newsletter subscribers or recurring visitors, to earn their trust and sell to them in the future. Compact Keywords targets WARM searchers. Blog SEO targets COLD searchers. Get it Read on Requires less time and money Easier for making sales, getting users, and getting leads: Visitors who land on Compact Keywords pages are already looking for what you offer. They need less convincing. Easier for SEO: Compact Keywords targets high-intent language most sites ignore ‐ meaning less competition and easier rankings. The result of this is You need less words per page (less work) You need less SEO backlinks (less money &amp; less work) Gives long-term success with Google Updates Compact Keywords gives searchers what Google wants : Direct, clear next steps. “You’re looking for what we offer ‐ here’s a button to buy it, use it, or get in touch.” Language to fill in gaps. Warm searchers are ready to act ‐ but most businesses don’t target the language they use. That means Google can’t recommend these businesses. Compact Keywords fixes this by matching intent with pages built to convert. Easily understood websites. Compact Keywords includes simple technical SEO lessons anyone can follow ‐ making your site easier for Google to crawl and parse, while also improving navigation for real people. Blog SEO, by comparison, usually gives searchers what Google doesn’t want : 3,000 word articles with a lot of fluff. Articles offer incomplete information or answers that are unnecessarily long. Targets the same language lots of other sites target. Doesn’t help Google fill in the gaps. Bloated content structures like /blog/, endless pagination, massive generic articles. Hurts usability and search engine understanding. Over the last several years, blog SEO has been hit by many Google Algorithm Updates! Don’t do it! William Bremer Over the last decade, I’ve seen Edward&#8217;s genuine excitement for marketing drive him to his standing as a leading voice in our industry. Brett Cohen Forbes | Executive Director, Production and Partner Experience Recommended by AI instead of disrupted by it Compact Keywords trains AI to recommend your brand for relevant scenarios. Somebody asks ChatGPT for a recommendation to something you have a Compact Keywords page on? ChatGPT is more likely to recommend your brand because your content addresses the specific need and shows up in the data AI models are trained on. When people say “SEO is dead,” they mean blog SEO is dead. ChatGPT has taken the place of answering “how, what, why, etc,” and AI Overviews in Google reduce clickthrough rate for blog SEO by 34% . Compact Keywords is NOT blog SEO. Diego Herrera Franco Edward is one of the most exceptional and dynamic digital marketers I have had the pleasure of working with. Yas Haque Omnicom (2nd largest publicly traded marketing agency) | Fmr. Head of SEO About your instructor 👋 Hi there! Hey! I&#8217;m Edward. Here&#8217;s some things about me: Did SEO at Dentsu International, one of the top 5 marketing agencies in the world. Had clients like P&amp;G and Luxottica . Mentor there went on to become Head of SEO at Omnicom, which, for a while, took the spot of the biggest publicly traded marketing agency (now it&#8217;s second). Started and ran the NYC SEO meetup group. Taught classes on SEO at Microsoft . With my own agency I’ve done SEO for dozens of startups and SMBs, including my own. Me in 2016 and 2017 teaching classes on SEO at the Times Square Microsoft offices. Hundreds of thousands of followers on Instagram and TikTok going viral with videos about SEO and digital marketing. View this post on Instagram A post shared by Edward Sturm (@edward.builds) View this post on Instagram A post shared by Edward Sturm (@edward.builds) Me quoted in Ahrefs . Feature about me trended #1 in HackerNoon a few days after it was released. Growth hacked my way into Forbes, The Verge, Entrepreneur Magazine and more. As I no longer take agency clients, I created Compact Keywords so founders, teams, and marketers could implement my unique method of doing SEO themselves. Edward is literally the evil genius of SEO (and all internet growth hacking). I’ve learned so much from him, and 11/10 recommend anything he does. Jason Levin Memelord Technologies (used by Coinbase, HubSpot) | Founder How this course gets you customers, users, and warm leads Introduction Why this method works and what to expect (1 video, 5:17) Critical Basics How to identify keywords that make money with less effort (2 videos, 13:50) The New SEO Real keyword examples that drive revenue and why blog SEO is dangerous (3 videos, 59:37) Visibility Foundations Making sure Google and AI can understand and index your website (1 template, 3 videos, 54:43) On-Page SEO How to make SEO landing pages that rank, get trained on by AI, and convert visitors (1 template, 3 videos, 51:42) On-Site SEO How to structure your website for purchase-intent pages (1 template, 3 videos, 35:51) Finding Compact Keywords My method for finding keywords that get you customers, users, and leads (2 templates, 9 videos, 2:16:32) Putting up Pages Putting together and publishing pages (1 template, 2 videos, 25:25) After Publishing a Page What real, lasting SEO results look like (2 videos, 22:39) Case Study Showing how few backlinks are needed to rank for high-intent searches (1 video, 14:05) Ranking Without Using a Website How to get sales with video SEO and user-generated content SEO (2 templates, 2 videos, 51:08) Link Building How to make search engines trust you and show your content (1 template, 5 videos, 1:54:48) Overview Prioritizing what’s most important for getting results (1 video, 10:45) Compact Conclusion Wrapping up (1 video, 2:48) BONUS Weekly breakdowns Examples in every niche Week 1 Local / Repairs (6:25) Week 3 Services / Legal (14:44) Week 5 Ecommerce / Petcare (13:27) Week 7 SaaS / AI (11:48) Week 9 Services / Crypto (15:22) Week 11 SaaS / Production (15:45) Week 13 Ecommerce / HomeTech (12:00) Week 15 Hyper-competitive SaaS (13:38) Week 2 Ecommerce / Bodycare (10:24) Week 4 Info Products / Marketing (16:05) Week 6 Local / Health (10:11) Week 8 Ecommerce / Wellness (15:28) Week 10 Ecommerce / Appliance (12:09) Week 12 Financial Services / Fintech (10:51) Week 14 Ecommerce / Outdoors (07:56) Angel Olavarria How it started Alejandro was the first customer of Compact Keywords. This was his feedback as he started the course: I can optimize these keywords for every channel! That is fireeeee. I’m in video 4 and I’m like a 16 year old kid with a PS2!!! This is changing my whole concept of what I will do with the site. Thank you!!! How it's going Now I have more than 20 pages ranking #1 and #2 for my company. Before Compact Keywords, I wasted thousands of dollars on SEO courses, trainings, and wasted time reading blogs. Compact Keywords is best training you’re going to find. It’s updated. And it’s working now, in the AI era. To me, Compact Keywords is not a course. It’s your method. It’s your blueprint. It’s the system you need to rank a website. Alejandro Morelli I have been working in SEO for over five years and have learned a lot of new things thanks to Edward’s course. I also really appreciate that I could email him with questions and receive feedback. Thank you, Edward! Victor Mooren Great course Edward has restored my faith in SEO. I thought AI had killed it. &mdash; Buymoda.net (@realbuymoda) July 11, 2025 I&#8217;m currently in the “On Site SEO&#8221; section. I&#8217;m already so glad I paid the money. Each lesson is DENSE with information. I knew a little bit about SEO beforehand, but I still get so much out of each lesson. You&#8217;re giving years&#8217; worth of experience boiled down into 15-30 minute lessons, with no filler or fluff. I feel like I&#8217;m gaining a new super power. Jason Leibler Kurt Xu I purchased Compact Keywords three weeks ago and already benefited a lot from it. It’s like a shortcut to learning SEO, saving you time and money. Kurt Xu I bought Edward&#8217;s course a couple months ago. Recently I got my first sale from my high-ticket dropshipping store. The sale was $500 . I did the bare minimum just to test the strategy, just to see if the little things work. Now that I see it actually works, I’m going all in. Knowing SEO is insanely practical and lucrative right now, the ROI is insane on this. It&#8217;s definitely worth the price. Kristijonas Grigauskas Kristijonas Grigauskas Frequently asked questions Who is this for? This method of SEO works for any niche and any brand . I&#8217;ve personally done this method for a variety of niches, from edtech to self-improvement. I&#8217;ve seen it work for many SaaS products. I&#8217;ve seen it work for service-based companies like agencies. It works well for startups, mid-sized businesses, and enterprise. My niche is small - will this work in my niche? Compact Keywords is EVEN BETTER in small niches. A good deal of Compact Keywords is identifying keywords that are not targeted properly and then simply targeting them properly. In small niches, the competition is a lot less savvy so MANY MORE money keywords are left sitting in the open, under-targeted. Is this lifetime access? Yes, it is. Do I need any tools to do this method? Yes. The SEO tool I share in the program is Moz , which has a tier that is $49/month and can do everything necessary. You can also get Moz for one month, use it to collect data and QA pages, then stop the subscription. If you already have a subscription to another popular SEO software suite, such as Ahrefs or Semrush, this will work too. The Compact Keywords method is flexible, and many SEO tools can do what is required. How often is Compact Keywords updated? Compact Keywords is updated often. If something needs to be changed or added, then it is promptly changed or added. Are there refunds? Yes, I want everybody to have a great experience with this course. Please see the refund policy for more. Can I pay in installments? Yes. At checkout, select USD to view options for splitting your purchase into multiple payments with Klarna or Afterpay/Clearpay. Please note these options are only available when paying in USD and may not be offered in every region. Do I need to have a website to