https://www.instagram.com/reel/DSQnlsPDChs/?igsh=N284d3d5OTRqNGM2,Brands to show in GPT SEO,"How brands can get shown more in ChatGPT. Go to ChatGPT, put in your prompt. Right click, inspect. Go to network. In the URL, copy what comes after /c/. Paste it in the filter. Now refresh the page. Click the orange brackets with the code you just put in. Go to response. Search the code for the word “queries”. Now you can see what ChatGPT searched the web with. Use the language that ChatGPT is searching with, put it in your content as H2 sections, or create entirely new pieces of content for exactly what ChatGPT is searching. That is how you get shown more in ChatGPT. And to learn my exact method of doing SEO that gets paying customers, go to compactkeywords.com",,,,
https://www.instagram.com/reel/DSS1I6cgSV2/?igsh=YXo1MXFzY29jOGdu,How to make a UGC portfolio,"I haven’t had to pitch in over a year. Brands find me, I don’t find them !! 👀 Here’s exactly how I built a UGC portfolio that makes brands want to work with me ⬇️ 1. I ALWAYS update it with my latest work. Any time I wrap a collaboration that really feels like my best or most recent style, I immediately add it to my portfolio. Keeping it fresh and relevant means that if a brand comes across it tomorrow, it reflects exactly where my content is today ✨ 2. I show a wide range of content types! My portfolio includes everything from talking head ads and testimonials to aesthetic lifestyle videos, product demonstrations, and trend-based concepts. The more range you show, the easier it is for a brand to visualize how you can fit into their marketing strategy - and that’s when they reach out first 🫣 3. My portfolio feels like me 💅🏻 My fonts, colors, and editing style are consistent throughout, so even though the videos are all different, the branding feels cohesive and intentional. It’s unique, it stands out, and it reflects my personal taste and creative direction. If you’re ready to make your portfolio stand out, here are a few action steps you can take ⤵️ – Add your most recent work that truly represents your current quality and creative direction – Offer specific things in your portfolio like retainers, trend packages, or A/B tester bundles – Make sure no two videos look or feel the same - variety is what sells you – Post your portfolio on TikTok (mine has gone viral multiple times 👀) – Update your branding to reflect you: the colors, fonts, and tone that make your content instantly recognizable Your portfolio should make brands want to reach out before you ever have to pitch. When it’s built with intention and personality, the right clients always find you 🤍",,,,
